# **Initiator Journey** {#initiator-journey}

**Step 1:** The Initiator **logs in** to the SignDesk application using the provided credentials.  
![][image2]

**Step 2:** The Initiator is redirected to the dashboard. To initiate a new document, the Initiator has to click on the **New Document** button present on the top right corner of the screen.  
![][image3]

**Step 3:** A drop-down menu appears. The Initiator has to select either one of the options based on the requirement.  
![][image4] 

**Step 4:** The Initiator has two options for document creation: 

* Upload  (Upload existing files from your local storage).  
* Templates (Use SignDesk’s standardized templates).

Select the **Upload** option and upload the document either by using the **Drag & Drop or** by clicking on the **Browse File** button.  
**![][image5]**   
**Step 5:** Once the document is uploaded, the **Document Title** will be automatically filled in based on the document name. Adding a description is optional. Click on the **Next** button to proceed.  
**![][image6]**

**Step 6:** (This step is optional) The Initiator can enable the toggle button to add the stamping services for the workflow if necessary. If not, click on the **Next** button to proceed.  
**![][image7]**

**Step 7:** The Initiator has to select the **Electronic Signature** as the signature type. To add a stakeholder to the workflow click on the **Add Stakeholder** button.  
**![][image8]**

**Step 8:** A popup appears, the Initiator has to select **Electronic** as the mode of signature. Fill in the necessary stakeholder details and click on the **Add** button to proceed.  
**![][image9]**

**Step 9:** A popup appears depicting the successful addition of the Signer. Click on the **Done** button to proceed.  
**![][image10]**

**Step 10:** The Initiator can add multiple signers by clicking on the **Add Stakeholder** button if needed. If not click on the **Next** button to proceed.  
**![][image11]**

**Step 11:** (This step is optional) In the settings section, the Initiator can fill in the necessary details if needed. If not, click on the **Next** button to proceed.  
**![][image12]**

**![][image13]**

**Step 12:**  The summary of the progress of the document can be viewed under the **Activity Logs**. Next, click on the **Proceed** button.  
**![][image14]**

**Step 13:** A success popup appears depicting that the signer has been notified. Click on the **Done** button to proceed.  
**![][image15]**

# **Signer Journey** {#signer-journey}

**Step 1:** An email invitation to sign the document is received by the signer at the provided email address. The signer has to click on the **Sign Document** button to proceed.  
![][image16]

**Step 2:** The signer is redirected to the SignDesk portal where the document preview is displayed. The signer has to click on the **Consent checkbox** and then click on the **Proceed** button.  
![][image17]  
**Step 3:** The signer can select any of the provided options to choose the signature for the document: 

* Signature (Available signature appearances)  
* Draw (Draw a custom signature)   
* Upload (Upload the desired signature from your local storage)

After choosing the signature for the document, click on the **Proceed** button.  
![][image18]  
**Step 4:** Next, the signer has to enter the OTP which is sent to the provided email address. Click on the **Sign now** button to proceed.   
**![][image19]**  
**Step 5:** A popup appears depicting that the **Document signed successfully**. Click on the **Okay** button to proceed.  
**![][image20]**

**Step 6:** Next, the signature is affixed to the document. The signer can download the signed document by clicking on the **Download** button.   
![][image21]  
**Step 7:** The signed document and the audit document are sent to the provided signer email address.  
![][image22]
